<br />
<br />=P   Why not?
<br />
<br />Anyway... I'm a little confused.  Is it <em>really</em> that MMC3 can't access 1MB?  Or is it just that no boards have that much PRG on them?  Like... does the MMC3 just not have enough pinouts?
<br />
<br />I'm not really very knowledgable when it comes to hardware.  I tried making sense of the pinout on <a href="http://www.tripoint.org/kevtris/mappers/mmc3/index.html" class="postlink">kevtris' page</a>, and it looks like it has pins going up to PRG A18... but wouldn't that make the cap 256K?  Obviously I'm misunderstanding because games have more than that.

		

